<p>Neat: The new JSON decoder by Géza Herman was merged onto the master branch: <a href="https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs.git/commit/?id=a5df4d92e37a176396577ac901b85025a6952376" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="ellipsis">git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emac</span><span class="invisible">s.git/commit/?id=a5df4d92e37a176396577ac901b85025a6952376</span></a>.  This replaces the Jansson encoder added in Emacs 27, dropping a dependency and speeding up the code by avoiding the allocation of intermediate objects.  This matters for people who use chatty LSP servers that send a lot of JSON code that has to be parsed, and allegedly improves the performance by a factor of 8.</p><p>Mattias Engdegård also wrote a JSON encoder: <a href="https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs.git/commit/?id=890edfd2bb8fd79730919972cc82811b73c7f572" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="ellipsis">git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emac</span><span class="invisible">s.git/commit/?id=890edfd2bb8fd79730919972cc82811b73c7f572</span></a></p><p>Background: <a href="https://mail.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2024-03/msg00244.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="ellipsis">mail.gnu.org/archive/html/emac</span><span class="invisible">s-devel/2024-03/msg00244.html</span></a>.</p><p><a class="mention hashtag" href="https://emacs.ch/tags/emacs" rel="tag">#<span>emacs</span></a></p>